        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>E. H. ELDRIDGE&#44;<lb/> MANAGER.<lb/></p>
            <p>Charles Roesch AND Sons&#39;<lb/>
                Popular Market House&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>Cor. Maryland and Atlantic Aves.<lb/></p>
            <p><hi rend="underline">City Dressed Meats of all kinds<lb/> and Everything appertaining<lb/> to a First&#45;class Market House</hi>.<lb/></p>
            <p>PHILADELPHIA STORES&#58;<lb/> ABATTOIR STOCK YARDS&#44; 31st and Market Streets&#44;<lb/> and 2nd and Poplar Streets.<lb/></p>
            <p>Atlantic City&#44; N. J.&#44; May 20<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1890<lb/></p>
            <p>S Morais Esq<lb/>
                Reverend Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>A years<lb/> experience in Atlantic City has impressed<lb/> me deeply that Judaism is gradually<lb/> waning away for the want of a<lb/> Teacher in Israel as in days before<lb/> All other Denominations are represented<lb/> here&#44; both white and black but the<lb/> Hebrews can not muster sufficient<lb/> courage to have a place of Worship<lb/> and a leader to guide them.  The<lb/> youth of Atlantic have a very slight&#44;<lb/> If indeed any knowledge of the<lb/> Religion of their Fathers and the<lb/> Fathers and Mothers of Israel justify<lb/> themselves that they are doing the<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>best they can by almost doing nothing<lb/> Atlantic numbers about 25 Jewish<lb/> families and with the exception<lb/> of Rosh Hashanna&#44; and Yom Kippur<lb/> there are no services here the entire<lb/> winter.  In Summer there are services<lb/> occasionally at Koopmans.  There<lb/> is more style than Religion exhibited<lb/> there but even as little as it is&#44; It<lb/> is better than nothing.  We have some<lb/> here who would willingly contribute<lb/> if some one else was to make the<lb/> start but they have not moral<lb/> courage enough to start themselves<lb/> Since my advent here I have done<lb/> what I could towards procuring<lb/> Kosher meat and at least on that<lb/> score I feel as If it may lead to<lb/> better results hereafter.  Certain<lb/> parties who had entirely discarded<lb/> Kosher meat were through my influence<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>and perseverance prevailed upon to<lb/> buy it if they could get it.  My<lb/> position does not permit me to do<lb/> all I should desire but If I can<lb/> be instrumental in raising and<lb/> upholding Judaism&#44; there is nothing<lb/> dearer to me.  The disbelievers in the<lb/> Holy One of Israel send missionaries<lb/> to all countries to make converts<lb/> for their Religion&#44; why could not the<lb/> Jewish Theological Seminary do some&#45;<lb/>thing similar&#63;  I appeal to you<lb/> as the Head and front of the Institution<lb/> to formulate a plan whereby Judaism<lb/> in small town and cities could<lb/> be benefitted<sic></sic> and&#44; led to respecting<lb/> their Religion the same as all other<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="4"/>
            <p>denominations.  Mr Jacob Rosenbaum<lb/> offers to procure for us a Hall free<lb/> of charge&#44; and to lend his assistance<lb/> in every shape to a project whereby<lb/> Atlantic City Jews and visitors<lb/> to the Seashore could have a place<lb/> of worship all the year around and<lb/> where the rising youth could be<lb/> instructed in their own Religion<lb/> My suggestions are that a visit<lb/> should be paid by some young<lb/> minister of the College&#44; and the<lb/> groundwork of starting a congregation<lb/> be his aim and object&#44; whoever<lb/> undertakes it can be assured<lb/> of all expense and hospitable treatment<lb/> I can not say everything in this<lb/> communication but desire an<lb/> opinion from you and If possible<lb/> assistance towards furthering the<lb/> object in view.  My confidence<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="5"/>
            <p>in your sincerity and piousness<lb/> leads me to hope that you will<lb/> encourage my plan and assist<lb/> to build an altar here where<lb/> the name of Jehovah can be<lb/> sanctified and glorified<lb/></p>
            <p>Your most respectful servant<lb/> Isaac Brylawski<lb/> 114 Nth Maryland Ave<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="6"/>
            <p>Chas. Roesch &#38; Sons&#39;<lb/>
                CENTRAL MARKET&#44;<lb/>
                Cor. Atlantic and Maryland Aves.&#44;<lb/>
                ATLANTIC CITY&#44; N. J.<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev S. Morais<lb/>
                525 Nth 5th St<lb/>
                Phila<lb/></p>
            </body>
